Observation of heatmap¶

Heatmap The heatmap is two dimensional representation of data in which values by representaion by colour. 1: See there We have +1 to -1 scale for colour.In these graph dark blue color represent the max values present there and faint color value represent the min value present at there. 2: Heatmap is used to checking the which feature is +ve or -ve correlated to each other. 3: In these heatmap Total profit is highly correlated to unit sold,unit price,unit cost,total Revenue,total cost.
